Uniform dark-matter zoom example with gas generation and EAGLE physics.

This example uses a standalone deterministic DM-only IC generator tuned for
EAGLE-like mass scales, then enables gas generation (`generate_gas_in_ics`) and
runs with the EAGLE model stack in a zoom configuration.

The setup is tuned for:

- ZoomRegion:bkg_top_level_cells = 8,
- ZoomRegion:zoom_top_level_depth = 2,
- a zoom extent spanning the central 2x2x2 background cells,
- region_pad_factor = 1.1.

Important: the parameter file for this example is configured for the
EAGLE-XL subgrid model (`--with-subgrid=EAGLE-XL`), not the legacy EAGLE
subgrid configuration.

The IC setup targets a post-split high-resolution DM mass of ~9.7e6 Msun.
Both zoom cells and non-central background top-level cells are populated with
the same fixed number of particles per cell (64), and particle masses are then
set from mass conservation in each region.

The run script fetches required EAGLE tables if they are missing.
